---
layout: base.njk
---
{# ABOUTME: Home page — single-page layout: hero, about, gallery (from collection), contact. #}

<section id="home">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero">
      <div>
        <p class="section-label">Art · Décor · Rare Books</p>
        <h1>For People Building Interesting Spaces</h1>
        <p>Curated pieces with a story — art, decorative objects, and rare
          illustrated books for the curious collector.</p>
        <p><a href="#contact" role="button">Visit Me In Person</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-media">
        <span>Featured piece</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label">My Story</p>
    <h2>Why I Do This</h2>
    <p>I think interesting people build interesting spaces. And interesting spaces
      need pieces with a story — things that make you curious, that start
      conversations, that surprise you because you're just now waking up to the
      idea that beauty comes in many forms.</p>
    <p>We all contain multitudes. Your space should, too.</p>
    <p>Mass market art and decor can be lovely. I've certainly bought plenty of it
      and liked it well enough. But there's nothing like going on a treasure hunt
      and coming home with something you're genuinely excited about. And in today's
      world of AI everything, I'm even more drawn to things that were created for
      humans, by humans.</p>
    <p>I hunt for the pieces that feel rare and thoughtful — objects with a real
      maker's hand behind them. The things that catch my eye usually have something
      unexpected about them, a weird angle, a color that shouldn't work but does.
      I'm drawn to work that has texture, personality, and won't apologize for being
      strange.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="gallery">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label">Collection</p>
    <h2>Featured Pieces</h2>
    {% if collections.gallery | length %}
    <div class="gallery-grid">
      {%- for item in collections.gallery | reverse %}
      <a class="gallery-item" href="{{ item.url }}">
        {% if item.data.image %}
          <img src="{{ item.data.image }}" alt="{{ item.data.title }}" loading="lazy">
        {% else %}
          <span class="gallery-item__placeholder">{{ item.data.title }}</span>
        {% endif %}
        {% if item.data.sold %}<span class="gallery-item__sold">Sold</span>{% endif %}
      </a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <p>The catalogue is being photographed. Check back soon.</p>
    {% endif %}
  </div>
</section>

<section id="contact" class="contact">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label">Visit</p>
    <h2>Find Me In Person</h2>
    <p>I'm in residence at {{ site.address.locatedWithin }} in {{ site.address.city }}, {{ site.address.state }}. That's where you'll find the real magic.</p>

    <div class="contact-grid">
      <div class="contact-block">
        <h3>Location</h3>
        <address>
          <strong>{{ site.address.locatedWithin }}</strong><br>
          {{ site.address.street }}<br>
          {{ site.address.city }}, {{ site.address.state }} {{ site.address.zip }}<br><br>
          <a href="tel:{{ site.phone | replace('(', '') | replace(')', '') | replace(' ', '') | replace('-', '') }}">{{ site.phone }}</a>
        </address>
        {% if site.maps %}
        <p class="social-links">
          <a href="{{ site.maps.apple }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple Maps</a>
          <a href="{{ site.maps.google }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Maps</a>
          <a href="{{ site.maps.waze }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Waze</a>
        </p>
        {% endif %}
      </div>

      <div class="contact-block">
        <h3>Hours</h3>
        <table class="hours">
          {%- for slot in site.hours %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ slot.days }}</td>
            <td>{{ slot.time }}</td>
          </tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="contact-block">
        <h3>Also Online</h3>
        <p>Follow my work and discoveries, or shop the collection from home.</p>
        <div class="social-links">
          {% if site.social.instagram %}<a href="{{ site.social.instagram }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Instagram</a>{% endif %}
          {% if site.social.chairish %}<a href="{{ site.social.chairish }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Shop on Chairish</a>{% endif %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
